                                <meta
                                    itemprop="reviewBody"
                                    content="I purchased the camera through the Polaroid website and it arrived with a defective viewfinder display. After days of going back and forth with Polaroid I was finally able to return it. Almost a month passed before I received the replacement. It also arrived with a defect--a thick, black hair on the inside of the viewfinder window and also a number of black specs. I should return this camera, too, but I don't want to wait another month for a replacement. These two issues make me wonder about quality control at Polaroid and if the cameras are being inspected. In terms of the images the camera produces and the ease of use I am pleased with the I-2. It is worth the money and the photographing experience and image quality far surpasses the Now+."
                                />
